Hi Tamar

I refer to the email of Adam

Yes it is possible to take out a loan for the existing portfolio and do the
investment in the same portfolio with the same
strategy Focus Mandate CHF.

We double the existing investment from CHF 1,3 Mio. to CHF 2,6 Mio.

For this we would make a loan for 6 months (roll-over) for the terms
condition of 0.6% p.a. (normal is 1%) and the loan
will be in a sup. Account for performance reasons.

Should you wish to do this we need the following documents sign and from
you and we need to have the original by post.

Look forward to a positive information and have a good day.

Best regards,

Maya











*From:* Adam Marash <adam@marash.net>




*Sent:* Mittwoch, 19. August 2020 18:17


*To:* Fankhauser-Fieramonte Maya H. <maya.fankhauser@vontobel.com>


*Subject:* Leverage on portfolio?







Maya Hello,











I hope you had a good vacation.













Based on our current outlook, we'd like to review our options with debt. To
get an idea about this, can you tell me: if we were to take out a loan
against the existing portfolio and put the loaned funds into the same

portfolio, how much leverage could we achieve and at what terms?













Thanks,













Adam










